modules.description: Handles signing and encoding of payloads using HMAC with SHA-256 or SHA-512, accepting a list of string pairs as input. Produces a signed JWT token by applying the specified algorithm to the payload. Supports direct use in authentication flows where secure, compact tokens are required.

This module offers functions for encoding, decoding, and verifying JSON Web Tokens (JWTs), with capabilities to construct headers, payloads, and signatures while extracting claims. It works with structured data types such as headers, payloads represented as key-value pairs, algorithms, and token representations, enabling precise manipulation of JWT components. Use cases include authentication workflows, secure data exchange, and token validation where cryptographic operations and claim verification are required.
